"It's not over, until I said it's over. "

After losing almost 70kgs during Covid, I found myself putting it all back in the last 3 years. 

The trolls subsequently came, but most importantly I felt as I I have disappointed so many people who were inspired from my previous weight loss process. 

I see so many young people falling into the trap of hunger suppression pills, sachets, weight loss cream and drinks that is supposed to make you small. I beg all of you to let that go and hit the gym. I had to learn it the hard way. 

Took me a while to finally put this out - but this time, this journey is going to work out.  It's going to be really long journey, but we'd get there soon enough. 

Special thanks to @vivarma16 and @resshmamohan for always telling it as it is and getting my ass back to the gym. Will forever more be grateful.
Every guy on my feed right now.
To everyone who complains of not getting the Deepavali feel anymore. Share this with them.
